  "texts": [
    "The results of this comparison, as shown in Figure 4, clearly demonstrate the impact of adding task-specific adaptation modules.",
    "Notably, the integration of these modules results in a substantial improvement in the accuracy-efficiency trade-off during parameter-efficient fine-tuning.",
    "This enhancement indicates the ability of the task-specific modules to effectively untangle the parameter space involved in MTL.",
    "Consequently, this leads to positive knowledge sharing during the finetuning process, significantly boosting the performance of each downstream task.",
    "Effect of Various Backbone Adaptation Locations: As mentioned in Subsection 3.2, we insert low-rank decom-0.5 0.0 0.5 1.0 1.5 2.0 2.5Relative Improvement to Single-Task Fine Tuning (%) position modules in four different locations in the Hierarchical Transformer encoder: 1) the feed-forward layers in the MLP block (FC1 and FC2), 2) the QKV layer, and 3) the projection layer."
